\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon$
\end_inset

 and for all 
\begin_inset Formula $x\in X$
\end_inset

, there exists an 
\begin_inset Formula $N(x)$
\end_inset

 such that 
\begin_inset Formula $k\ge N(x)$
\end_inset

 implies 
\begin_inset Formula $|f_{k}(x)-f(x)|<\varepsilon$
\end_inset

.
 
